snippet.title: Saturn Longplay [182] Keio Flying Squadron 2 (EU)
snippet.description:
http://www.longplays.org

Played by: SCHLAUCHI

Keio Flying Squadron 2 (Keiō Yūgekitai: Katsugeki-hen) is a 1996 Japanese video game for the Sega Saturn. Developed by Victor Entertainment, it is a direct sequel to Keio Flying Squadron. While the first game is a side-scrolling shoot 'em up, the second game is a platformer with shooter sections.

Like the first game, the second game refers to Japanese culture, both ancient and modern simultaneously.
